{{Infobox company |name = Chef2Chef.net |logo = chef2chef.png |logo_size = 250px |type = [[Privately held|Privately Held Company]] |foundation = [[Foster City, CA]] |location = [[Foster City, CA]], [[United States|USA]] |key_people = Seth Restaino, General manager; Alisa Stoudt; Managing Editor; Tracy Viselli, Social Media Manager |industry = Culinary education and information |homepage = http://www.chef2chef.net }}
'''Chef2Chef.net''' is a [[culinary]] website with [[recipes]], columns, food-related [[internet forum|forums]] and [[blogs]], chef interviews, and online cooking classes. The site has an index and search tool that includes [[culinary schools]] in the U.S. and around the globe with information available by city, state, and country. Chef2Chef has a restaurant and food services employment job board for job seekers and employers and a Marketplace with equipment, services, and supplies for the chef consumer and food service organizations. The site also posts information about industry [[scholarships]] and [[grants]], food-related [[festivals]] and events, and [[farmers markets]] across the U.S. and [[Canada]].
==Background==
Chef2Chef was co-founded in 1999 by David and Pamela Nelson and partners, Fred and Margie Roosli.<ref>[http://chefdavidnelson.com/bio.htm http://chefdavidnelson.com/bio.htm] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100225193718/http://chefdavidnelson.com/bio.htm |date=February 25, 2010 }}</ref> [[Quinstreet|QuinStreet, Inc.]], an online marketing company based in [[Foster City, CA]] acquired the site in October 2006.
==Recognition==
In 2002, [[PC Magazine]] Website Rover editors rated Chef2Chef.net the Editor's Choice of their top eight culinary websites.<ref>[https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,63616,00.asp PC Magazine Web site Reviewer]</ref>
