{{Infobox recurring event | name = east forum Berlin | native_name = | logo = East forum Berlin logo.png | logo_caption = | frequency = Annually | location = [[Berlin]], Germany | first = 2013 by [[Achim Oelgarth]] and [[Rainer Lindner]] and since 2015 with [[Ivonne Bollow]] | last = April 2015 | participants = 250 to 350 from 30 countries | organised = [[UniCredit]], [[METRO GROUP]], [[:de:Ost-Ausschuss der Deutschen Wirtschaft|Ost-Ausschuss der Deutschen Wirtschaft]], [[Federal State of Berlin]] | people = | website = {{URL|http://www.eastforum-berlin.de}} }} {{DISPLAYTITLE:east forum Berlin}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}} Every year, the '''east forum Berlin''' brings together [[opinion leader]]s from the political and business worlds in the East and the West to discuss challenges and [[Business opportunity|opportunities]] faced by the economic area from Lisbon to Vladivostok and beyond. It was founded in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|title = east forum Berlin schafft neue Plattform für europäische Wirtschaftsdebatten|url = https://www.berlin.de/sen/wirtschaft/presse/pressemitteilungen/2013/pressemitteilung.146793.php|website = www.berlin.de|date = 2014-07-12|accessdate = 2016-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Beratergruppe Ukraine {{!}} Präsentation beim 2. east forum Berlin „Eastern Partnership countries between East and West: Perspectives and challenges“|url = http://www.beratergruppe-ukraine.de/wordpress/de/praesentation-beim-2-east-forum-berlin-eastern-partnership-countries-between-east-and-west-perspectives-and-challenges/|website = www.beratergruppe-ukraine.de|accessdate = 2016-01-04}}</ref>
The overall aim of the east forum Berlin is to facilitate dialogue in order to overcome barriers for prosperity, to exchange know-how and intensify networks. In addition, this international event is an opportunity to present Berlin as a vibrant location of political and economic debate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Georgia participates in 3rd East Forum Berlin 2015|url = http://agenda.ge/news/33755/eng|website = agenda.ge|accessdate = 2016-01-04}}</ref>
east forum Berlin 2016 took place during Germany's [[OSCE]] Chairmanship<ref>http://www.osce.org/cio</ref> in the middle of new deadlocks and new dynamics that characterise the transforming economic and political realities in the region from Europe to Asia. The two opposing trends are embedded in new division lines leading to an unfamiliar status quo of alienation. Secondly, they are surrounded by recently formed alliances consisting of as yet poorly known stakeholders, which create new spheres of influence. These dynamics offer potential for [[economic growth|growth]] but also involve geopolitical and geo-economic challenges for all stakeholders in the region.
